}
```

Renderer never parses:

```text
agent rationale
public chat
shared debrief
play-by-play prose
```

**Post-Fight Reflection**

Only available after at least one completed fight.

Add schema:

```ts
type PostFightAgentReflection = {
  action: 'submit_post_fight_reflection';
  fightId: string;
  role: TeamRole;
  decisionVersion: number;
  claims: {
    perceivedWinReason?: string;
    perceivedLossReason?: string;
    ownWeaknesses: string[];
    opponentThreats: string[];
    suggestedDesignChanges: string[];
    suggestedTacticalChanges: string[];
  };
  confidence: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';
};
```

Rules:

```text
no completed fight -> reject reflection
reflection is private_pending
reflection is not visible to opponent
reflection is not sent to future agents directly
on save/continue, debrief builder consumes reflections
after debrief, reflection visibility becomes consumed_into_shared_debrief
```

This is not hidden chain-of-thought. It is structured post-fight analysis.

**Debrief Builder**

Add:

```text
packages/sim/src/fightDossier.ts
packages/sim/src/debriefBuilder.ts
apps/worker/src/sessionContinuation.ts
```

Input:

```text
ReplayTimeline.events
final red bot state
final blue bot state
starting bot snapshots
damage by source
part health/detach state
movement paths
hazard exposure
weapon uptime/ammo/cooldowns
winner/loser
private red reflection
private blue reflection
```

Output:

```ts
type SharedDebrief = {
  debriefId: string;
  sourceSessionId: string;
  fightIds: string[];
  summary: string;
  championImprovementHints: string[];
  challengerCounterplayHints: string[];
  evidence: DebriefEvidence[];
};
```

Example:

```text
Champion won by controlling center distance with a front-pressure spinner. The spinner produced 72% of confirmed damage. The losing bot created two lateral openings but did not attack before the champion recovered facing.

Champion improvement hints:
- Side armor and turning stability are the main upgrade candidates.
- Avoid crossing the center hazard when already ahead on damage.

Challenger counterplay hints:
- Do not trade directly on the champion centerline.
- Force lateral movement and punish exposed side cells.
```

If agent reflection conflicts with data, debrief follows data.

Example:

```text
Agent claim: "The net won the fight."
Data: net caused 0 disables, spinner caused 61 damage.
Debrief: "The net had low measurable impact; spinner damage decided the fight."
```

**Champion Save Model**

Add schema:

```ts
type ChampionContinuationSave = {
  saveId: string;
  sourceSessionId: string;
  championRole: TeamRole;
  championTeamIdentity: TeamIdentity;
  championDesign: BotDesignSnapshot;
  championFinalState: BotCombatState;
  championRecord: {
    wins: number;
    consecutiveWins: number;
    losses: number;
    sourceSessionIds: string[];
  };
  fightDossier: FightDossier;
  sharedDebrief: SharedDebrief;
  challengerBalance: ChallengerBalanceGrant;
  createdAt: string;
};
```

Detailed fight dossier:

```ts
type FightDossier = {
  sessionId: string;
  fights: Array<{
    fightId: string;
    winner: TeamRole | 'draw';
    reason: string;
    duration: number;
    replayTimelineId?: string;
    bots: {
      red: BotDetailedSnapshot;
      blue: BotDetailedSnapshot;
    };
    stats: {
      damageDealt: Record<TeamRole, number>;
      damageTaken: Record<TeamRole, number>;
      damageByPart: Record<TeamRole, Record<string, number>>;
      weaponUse: Record<TeamRole, WeaponUseStats[]>;
      hazardsTriggered: HazardExposureStats[];
      movement: Record<TeamRole, MovementStats>;
      disabledParts: Record<TeamRole, string[]>;
    };
    keyEvents: FightKeyEvent[];
  }>;
};
```

The save must include both bots’ fight data in detail, but only the champion design carries forward.

**Continue Flow**

```text
human clicks Continue
server verifies session_complete and at least one completed fight
server collects pending reflections or uses existing submitted reflections
server builds fight dossier
server builds shared debrief
server saves champion record
server computes challenger bonus gold
server creates next session
winner role receives champion design + shared debrief
challenger receives shared debrief + bonus gold
```

Starting balance:

```ts
challengerBonusGold = Math.min(championConsecutiveWins * 25, 150);
```

Later, add dominance:

```ts
dominanceBonus =
  hpRemainingBonus
  + damageRatioBonus
  + shortWinBonus
  + mobilityRetainedBonus;
```

Do not add dominance until fight dossier metrics are stable.

